cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a novel mobile application that utilizes deep learning methods, specifically Convolutional Neural Networks, for automated water impurity detection. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves training a deep learning algorithm with a dataset, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves efficient analysis of the turbidity and transparency levels of water, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper involves the use of machine learning to estimate water quality, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
